I think it should be sufficient to replace
{code:java}
protected final static DateTime startingDateValue = new DateTime(1970, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0);{code}
with
{code:java}
protected final static DateTime startingDateValue = new DateTime(1970, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeZone.UTC)
        .withZoneRetainFields(DateTimeZone.getDefault());{code}
 

This is equivalent to the former for any normal zone, but doesn't fail for "odd" zone that skipped 1970-01-01 00:00:00 in its local time.
